Alright — this is the **advanced path 🔥 (recover + upgrade without reinstall)**
You *can* recover, but we need to **stop the uninstall flow and bring ODF back to normal reconcile**.

Right now your cluster is in a **half-deleted state**, so we fix that step by step.

---

# 🧠 What we will do

1. ❌ Stop deletion (remove finalizers)
2. ❌ Stop uninstall mode annotations
3. ✅ Bring StorageCluster back to “Ready”
4. ✅ Trigger reconcile
5. ✅ Let ODF upgrade remaining components

---

# ⚠️ Important

* This is **safe if Ceph data still exists** (your pods are running → good sign ✅)
* Do NOT delete PVs / OSDs

---

# 🚀 STEP 1 — Remove uninstall annotations

Your cluster has:

```text
uninstall.ocs.openshift.io/mode: graceful
uninstall.ocs.openshift.io/cleanup-policy: delete
```

👉 Remove them:

```bash
oc annotate storagecluster ocs-storagecluster \
-n openshift-storage \
uninstall.ocs.openshift.io/mode- \
uninstall.ocs.openshift.io/cleanup-policy-
```

---

# 🚀 STEP 2 — Remove deletion timestamp (CRITICAL)

👉 Remove finalizer so deletion stops:

```bash
oc patch storagecluster ocs-storagecluster \
-n openshift-storage \
--type=merge -p '{"metadata":{"finalizers":[]}}'
```

---

# 🚀 STEP 3 — Do same for CephCluster

```bash
oc patch cephcluster ocs-storagecluster-cephcluster \
-n openshift-storage \
--type=merge -p '{"metadata":{"finalizers":[]}}'
```

---

# 🚀 STEP 4 — Recreate finalizer (VERY IMPORTANT)

Now re-add proper finalizer so operator manages it again:

```bash
oc patch storagecluster ocs-storagecluster \
-n openshift-storage \
--type=merge -p '{"metadata":{"finalizers":["storagecluster.ocs.openshift.io"]}}'
```

---

# 🚀 STEP 5 — Restart ODF operator

```bash
oc delete pod -n openshift-storage -l name=odf-operator
```

(or)

```bash
oc rollout restart deploy/odf-operator-controller-manager -n openshift-storage
```

---

# 🚀 STEP 6 — Force reconcile

```bash
oc annotate storagecluster ocs-storagecluster \
-n openshift-storage \
odf.openshift.io/force-reconcile="$(date +%s)" --overwrite
```

---

# 🔍 STEP 7 — Verify recovery

```bash
oc get storagecluster -n openshift-storage
```

👉 Expected:

```text
PHASE: Ready ✅ (not Deleting)
```

---

